    {
      "name": "Cluster - PostgreSQL",
      "description": "PostgreSQL supports either a single primary node or a primary with one or more standby nodes.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Deploy",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// Auto-extract JOB_ID and credentials from plain-JSON deploy response (no encryption)",
                  "const encryptionKey = pm.variables.get('ENCRYPTION_KEY');",
                  "if (encryptionKey && encryptionKey.trim() !== '') { return; }",
                  "try {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (body && body.data) {",
                  "        if (body.data.id) {",
                  "            pm.collectionVariables.set('JOB_ID', body.data.id);",
                  "            console.log('[erawan] JOB_ID set to:', body.data.id);",
                  "        }",
                  "        if (body.data.secret) {",
                  "            const s = body.data.secret;",
                  "            if (s.postgres_user) pm.collectionVariables.set('PGSQL_DB_USER', s.postgres_user);",
                  "            if (s.postgres_password) pm.collectionVariables.set('PGSQL_DB_PASSWORD', s.postgres_password);",
                  "            console.log('[erawan] PGSQL_DB_USER set to:', s.postgres_user);",
                  "            console.log('[erawan] PGSQL_DB_PASSWORD auto-filled from deploy secret');",
                  "        }",
                  "    }",
                  "} catch(e) {}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              },
              "raw": "{\n  \"cluster_name\": \"{{CLUSTER_NAME}}\",\n  \"admin_username\": \"admin\",\n  \"admin_password\": \"\",\n  \"primary_ip\": \"{{PGSQL_PRIMARY_IP}}\",\n  \"standby_ips\": [],\n  \"new_user\": \"{{NEW_USER}}\",\n  \"new_user_password\": \"{{NEW_USER_PASSWORD}}\",\n  \"new_user_ssl_required\": true,\n  \"new_db\": \"{{NEW_DB}}\",\n  \"ssh_port\": 22,\n  \"postgres_port\": 5432,\n  \"postgres_version\": 16,\n  \"step_timeout_seconds\": 900\n}"
            },
            "description": "Starts a PostgreSQL/Patroni cluster deployment. Returns a job immediately (202 Accepted). Poll 'Get Job' to track progress.\n\nUse `standby_ips: []` for primary-only mode, or provide one or more standby IPs for HA mode.\n\nJOB_ID is auto-extracted from the response and stored as a collection variable.",
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://{{API_HOST}}:{{API_PORT}}/cluster/pgsql/deploy",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": [
                "{{API_HOST}}"
              ],
              "port": "{{API_PORT}}",
              "path": [
                "cluster",
                "pgsql",
                "deploy"
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Collect Metrics",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              },
              "raw": "{\n  \"port\": {{PGSQL_PROXY_PORT}},\n  \"node_ips\": [\"{{PGSQL_PRIMARY_IP}}\", \"{{PGSQL_STANDBY_IP_1}}\", \"{{PGSQL_STANDBY_IP_2}}\"],\n  \"user\": \"{{PGSQL_DB_USER}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{PGSQL_DB_PASSWORD}}\",\n  \"database\": \"postgres\",\n  \"ssl_mode\": \"require\",\n  \"connect_timeout\": 10,\n  \"patroni_port\": 8008,\n  \"categories\": [],\n  \"databases\": [],\n  \"limit\": 20\n}"
            },
            "description": "Collects live metrics from a running PostgreSQL/Patroni cluster.\n\n**Required:** `user`\n\n**Connection routing:**\n- `host` (optional) — HAProxy address; defaults to `PROXY_HOST` env var on the server (usually `127.0.0.1`)\n- `port` — HAProxy listen port for PostgreSQL traffic (e.g. 25432)\n- `node_ips` — list of all cluster member IPs; the collector calls `GET /leader` on each and auto-discovers the current primary for Patroni REST (`cluster`, `failover` categories). Required only when collecting those categories.\n\n**Optional:** `host`, `port` (default 5432), `password`, `database` (default `postgres`), `ssl_mode` (`disable`|`require`, default `disable`), `connect_timeout` (seconds, default 10), `patroni_port` (default 8008), `limit` (top-N for slow queries/latency, default 20), `from`/`to` (ISO 8601, filter failover events and slow queries)\n\n**`databases`** — optional list of database names to filter per-database results (connections by_database, slow queries, autovacuum workers, logical slot lag). Empty array = all databases. Response always includes `database_count` (total user databases, excluding templates).\n\n**`categories`** — empty array returns all; pick any subset:\n- `cluster` — Patroni HA state, DCS health, node roles, TTL/loop_wait\n- `uptime` — PostgreSQL process uptime\n- `failover` — Patroni timeline/failover history (supports `from`/`to` filter)\n- `connections` — active, idle, idle-in-transaction, lock-waiters, wait-event breakdown\n- `replication` — streaming lag (LSN pipeline), standby count, WAL config, slot lag\n- `performance` — TPS, cache hit ratio, temp files, checkpoint pressure, bgwriter stats\n- `query` — avg/p95/p99 latency, slow queries, lock/deadlock counts, scan efficiency\n- `maintenance` — autovacuum workers, XID wraparound age, logical slot lag, pg_locks",
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://{{API_HOST}}:{{API_PORT}}/cluster/pgsql/metrics",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": [
                "{{API_HOST}}"
              ],
              "port": "{{API_PORT}}",
              "path": [
                "cluster",
                "pgsql",
                "metrics"
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List Jobs",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://{{API_HOST}}:{{API_PORT}}/cluster/pgsql/jobs?limit=20",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": [
                "{{API_HOST}}"
              ],
              "port": "{{API_PORT}}",
              "path": [
                "cluster",
                "pgsql",
                "jobs"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "limit",
                  "value": "20"
                }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Job",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://{{API_HOST}}:{{API_PORT}}/cluster/pgsql/jobs/{{JOB_ID}}",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": [
                "{{API_HOST}}"
              ],
              "port": "{{API_PORT}}",
              "path": [
                "cluster",
                "pgsql",
                "jobs",
                "{{JOB_ID}}"
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Resume Job",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              },
              "raw": "{\n  \"admin_password\": \"\",\n  \"new_user_password\": \"{{NEW_USER_PASSWORD}}\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Resumes a failed PostgreSQL cluster job from the last completed step.\n\n- `admin_password` — leave empty to reuse the password stored from the original deploy\n- `new_user_password` — required when the job has a `new_user`",
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://{{API_HOST}}:{{API_PORT}}/cluster/pgsql/jobs/{{JOB_ID}}/resume",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": [
                "{{API_HOST}}"
              ],
              "port": "{{API_PORT}}",
              "path": [
                "cluster",
                "pgsql",
                "jobs",
                "{{JOB_ID}}",
                "resume"
              ]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "DB Manager - MySQL",
      "description": "Create and delete users and databases on a running MySQL cluster.\n\nAdmin credentials: use MYSQL_DB_USER / MYSQL_DB_PASSWORD (clusteradmin) from the deploy response, or any user with the required privileges.\n\nPrivilege model:\n- New users get SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, CREATE, DROP, ALTER, INDEX, REFERENCES on the specified database only\n- If no `database` is provided, the user is created with no database access\n- Users cannot drop other users (no CREATE USER privilege)\n- New databases are granted to all existing app users automatically",
